&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;GiveWell’s mission is to help people in need as much as we can by researching the most cost‑effective ways to save and improve lives, sharing our work openly, and directing donations to the programs we believe will do the most good. Our work, which focuses on global health and well-being, is funded by tens of thousands of donors who rely on our research to inform their giving. We’ve grown from directing $1.5 million in 2010 to directing more than $400 million in 2025—and we expect to direct more than $500 million in 2026. Through years of deliberate groundwork, we’ve been growing our research capacity and scope in order to direct substantially more funding to the most impactful opportunities we can find.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you&#39;re passionate about GiveWell&#39;s work but none of our currently open roles feel like a strong fit, we encourage you to submit your general information to our Talent Pool.&lt;/p&gt;
